-
what :: which :: something :: everything

-
how :: a :: why :: who

-
that :: whatever :: anything :: thing

Wir müssen wissen, was sicher ist und was nicht, was Wahrheit ist und was Unwahrheit und was richtig ist und was falsch.
We have to know what is safe and what is not safe, what is truth and what is not truth, and what is right and what is not right.

Wir achten was passt, was stimmt, was angemessen ist und was verändert werden muss.
We watch carefully: to see what is suited, what rings true, what is appropriate and what must be changed.

Nafi Sciences '(was nützlich ist) wird selbstbewusster zu produzieren, was zweifelhaft ablehnen würde.
Nafi Sciences' (which is useful) will produce self-confident, which would reject doubtful.

Vielleicht ist was drin, was wir gebrauchen können.
Might be something we can use inside.

Mr. Grey gab meinem Schwager was, was ihn völlig betrunken macht.
Mr Grey has given my brother-in-law something to make him appear drunk.

Ermitteln Sie, was in den aktuellen Leistungsverwaltungsprozessen funktioniert und was nicht.
Identify what works and what does not work in your current performance management processes.

Mit den Beurteilungen der Gesundheitsauswirkungen können wir feststellen, was hilft und was nicht.
With health impact assessments we can detect what works and what does not.

Diese Bekanntmachung wird aufführen, was bisher erreicht wurde und was noch zu tun ist.
That Communication will set out what has been achieved so far and what still remains to be done.

Hier brauchen wir Klarheit, was Legislative ist und was Exekutive.
We need to be clear in our own minds here about what is legislative and what is executive.

Schauen Sie nach, was sich geändert hat und was in naher Zukunft noch geplant ist.
Find out what changes we have made, and what other improvements you can expect to see in the near future.

Da ist der Fall, daß ein Bhikkhu, nur das sagt, was gutgesprochen, nicht das was armselig gesprochen ist, nur was recht, nicht was unrecht ist, nur was annehmbar, nicht was unannehmbar ist, nur was wahr, nicht was unwahr ist.
There is the case where a monk says only what it well-spoken, not what is poorly spoken; only what is just, not what is unjust; only what is endearing, not what is unendearing; only what is true, not what is false.

Ich habe dir was mitgebracht, was nützlich sein könnte.
I brought you something might come in handy.

Ich weiß was, was der junge Dale bloß vermutet.
I know something young Dale merely suspects.

Komm her, ich zeig dir was, was sie im Fernsehen nicht zeigen durften.
Come here, I want to show you something they wouldn't allow... on "World of Mystery".

Ich habe da was in meinem Rucksack, was unsere Chancen deutlich verbessern könnte.
I have something in my backpack, which could significantly improve our chances.

Du solltest noch was machen, aber ich weiß nicht mehr, was.
There's something I need you to do, but I can't think of what it is.

Das ist nur was, was was jeden Mittag passiert.
It's just something that - Happens at noon every day.

SpamKiller Appliances überwachen, was in das Netzwerk hereinkommt und was es verlässt.
SpamKiller appliances monitor what is entering and leaving the network.

Und was Besprechungen angeht, so interessiert Sie nur, was in Ihrem Kalender erscheint.
In fact, you don't care to see anything about meetings except what's in your calendar.

Im vorliegenden Fall ist einigen Mitgliedstaaten ganz offenbar nicht klar, was Rechtsstaatlichkeit ist und was Achtung der Menschenrechte bedeutet.
It is crystal clear therefore that, in the present case, some Member States do not understand what rule of law and respect for human rights mean.

